# Hugo build warning allowlist.
# Lines here are KNOWN-AND-ACCEPTED warnings from `hugo --printPathWarnings`
# or similar. CI fails on:
#   1. Any new warning line NOT in this allowlist (new noise)
#   2. Any line in this allowlist that NO LONGER appears in current build (dead allowlist line)
#
# Bidirectional check prevents silent rot after Hugo or theme upgrades.
#
# Empty by default: current build (Hugo 0.160.0, custom in-tree theme)
# produces zero warnings. If a future build introduces warnings, add the
# exact line here with a comment explaining why it's accepted.
#
# Refresh procedure: run `hugo --gc -e production --logLevel info 2>&1 | grep -i warn`,
# inspect each new warning, decide accept/fix.
